## Aio-Json

> Example

``` python
from zjson import AsyncClient

db = AsyncClient(name="db.json", directory="cache")

async def main():
    await db.set(
        key="key",
        value="value"
    )
    print(await db.get("key")) # value
    await db.set(
        key="key2",
        value=[1, 2, 3],
        expire=10 # expire after 10 seconds
    )
    await db.sleep(10)
    print(await db.get("key2")) # None

db.run(main())

```

### Installing

``` bash
pip3 install -U zjson
```

